                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso)"/>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from the Catechism, in Amharic.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">፭ቱ ንስሐ: ምንምን: ናቸው: ቢሉ: ፩ፊት: ያደረገውን: ሐጢአት: ክፋት: ማሰብ: ነው: ፪ ከፊት: ያደረገ(ውን) ሐጢአት: ክፋት: አስቦ: መአዘን: ማልቀስ: ነው:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT3851Hassab"/>, on moveable feasts and fasts
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#156v #180r"/>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Name of owner, erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#60"/>
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    blue yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark readings;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#123"/>
                    <desc>
                    blue and red yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–3
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#2v #12v #25v #43r #54v"/>
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#30v #47r #65r #68r #85v"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) and lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#73v"> line 10</locus><locus target="#127v"> line 11</locus><locus target="#128r"> line 5</locus>
                    <desc>
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#20v #26v #27v #78r"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#13r #15v #18r #21r #22r"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#3r #3v #4r #5r #6r"/>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line                    </desc>
                    </item>
